# ChemCheck App Store Environment Template

Use this as the release-environment checklist for the parked iOS shell. Do not commit real secrets or generated `.env*` files.

## Web Build Values

```bash
VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
VITE_DISABLE_AUTH_BYPASS=true
VITE_ENABLE_LOCALHOST_AUTH_BYPASS=false
VITE_IOS_SIM_AUTH_BYPASS=false
VITE_DISABLE_SERVICE_WORKER=false
```

## Clerk

```bash
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_replace_me
VITE_CLERK_PROXY_URL=https://clerk.chemcheck.xyz
VITE_CLERK_DOMAIN=clerk.chemcheck.xyz
```

Clerk dashboard checks:

- Production application uses `clerk.chemcheck.xyz`.
- iOS/WebView origins and redirect URLs are allowed.
- Development domain `game-sloth-45.clerk.accounts.dev` is not used for the App Store build.
- If Google, Facebook, or another third-party/social sign-in provider is enabled for iOS, Sign in with Apple is enabled too.

## Convex

```bash
VITE_CONVEX_URL=https://your-production-deployment.convex.cloud
CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT_ENV=production
```

Set `VITE_CONVEX_URL` to the exact production deployment host. This value is required for the native shell but is not a `WKAppBoundDomains` navigation entry unless the app actually navigates the WebView there.

## Billing

The parked iOS shell blocks Stripe checkout and Stripe portal actions in native iOS. Keep the PWA/web billing configuration separate from the App Store review decision.

If this build is only for existing ChemCheck accounts, leave Stripe checkout URLs out of the iOS release build:

```bash
VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
VITE_STRIPE_CHECKOUT_URL=
VITE_STRIPE_PORTAL_URL=
VITE_STRIPE_CANCEL_URL=
VITE_STRIPE_STARTER_PRICE_ID=
VITE_STRIPE_PRO_PRICE_ID=
VITE_STRIPE_BUSINESS_PRICE_ID=
```

If native iOS later sells digital ChemCheck access, replace this approach with Apple In-App Purchase before App Review.

## Monitoring

```bash
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=
SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=
```

Only set monitoring values that are valid for the production release. Keep private tokens in the build environment, not in Git.

## Native Toolchain

```bash
sudo xcode-select --switch /Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer
xcodebuild -version
xcodebuild -list -project ios/App/App.xcodeproj
```

## Release Gate

```bash
scripts/app-store-preflight.sh --full
```
